Anti-endomysial antibodies titer was 80 (normal is negative), anti-tissue transglutaminase IgA was positive 75 U/ml (normal <2.5 U/ml) and anti-tissue transglutaminase IgG was negative. Upper endoscopy was done with small intestinal biopsy. The duodenum showed scalloping and fissuring of the small bowel. The histopathology report of the small intestine showed severe villous atrophy grade IV withcrypt hyperplasia. OldMarsh-Oberhuber classification: Type 3c: Total villousatrophy with completely flat mucosa and increased intraepithelial lymphocytes.